## Next.js Standards

- Use the App Router (`app/`) for new routes; prefer Server Components by default
- Add `"use client"` only when browser APIs, event listeners, or React state are needed
- Co-locate route-specific components, hooks, and utilities within the route segment
- Use `next/image` for all images; never raw `<img>` tags
- Use `next/link` for internal navigation; never raw `<a>` tags
- Fetch data in Server Components using `fetch` with appropriate cache directives
- Use Route Handlers (`route.ts`) for API endpoints; validate input with Zod
